It's a lot less complicated than you think. Talent and Work, that's it. Both of these factors are under your control. Actually, one fuels the other. In order to develop talent, you need work. The more you work, the more talented you become. Other than that, reverse engineer the whole thing and ask yourself why you want to do this in the first place, hobby or business? If it's a hobby, cool, take it slow and enjoy. If it's to create a new business or accelerate an existing business, don't bother unless you're willing to put in the work. Valeria's built her audience to over 1.3M on YouTube and 500K on Instagram. I see first hand how much work it is. Not only is it not easy, but even if you hire a team to help you, it's still an overwhelming amount of work. Good luck!
